# Frontoffice UI architecture rules

## Dumb components only
- `components/**` are presentation-only.
  - Accept props + callbacks.
  - NO data fetching.
  - NO calling tRPC/React Query.
  - NO Clerk hooks.
  - NO direct access to repositories/services.

## Pages own data logic
- `app/**/page.tsx` (and route-level layout components) may:
  - call Clerk hooks
  - call React Query hooks
  - call tRPC client hooks
  - assemble data + callbacks and pass them down to screen/components.

## State management
- Use native React context (`useContext`) for app-level UI state.
- No Redux/Zustand/etc.

## Folder conventions (recommended)
- `components/ui/*`: primitives (buttons, inputs, dialogs) — pure UI.
- `components/screens/*`: screen components — still dumb; pages inject props.

